ch Lucien, Marcel, Leonide, Andre, Armand, Camille, Emile, Fernand, Firmin, Francois, Ghislaine, Normand.","English, French, Walloon, and Breton: variant of   Colin  . This surname is also found in the Flemish part of Belgium.","German: variant of   Kollin   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this."]},{"name":"Cullinan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Cormac.","Irish (Clare): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Cuileannáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cuileannán</i>’, from a diminutive of <i>Cuileann</i> (see   Cullen   2)."]},{"name":"Cullens","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Cullen  , with excrescent or genitival <i>-s</i>.","Dutch (Rotterdam): possibly an adaptation of English   Collins  ."]},{"name":"Cullin","meanings":["Irish (Longford and Roscommon) and English: variant of   Cullen  ."]}]},{"name":"Mór","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name from <i>mór</i> ‘large, great’. This was the commonest of all girls’ names in late medieval Ireland, and has continued in use in both Ireland and Scotland to the present day."],"variants":[]},{"name":"macNamara","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish:  see  McNamara  ."],"variants":[{"name":"McNamara","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Parnell, Aidan, Conor, Dermot, Brigid, Conan, James Patrick, Liam, Michael Patrick, Nuala, Ronan.","Irish and Manx: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Conmara</b>, a patronymic from <i>Cú Mhara</i>, a personal name composed of the elements <i>cú</i> ‘hound’ + <i>muir</i> (genitive <i>mara</i>) ‘sea’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mór macNamara Uí Collieann \"Cullen\" was born in 1197, in Ireland, her father, Caisin MacNamora, was 28 and her mother, Maud Brady, was 28. She had at least 4 sons with Conchobhar an Suidane O Briain. She died on 25 June 1238, in her hometown,